               <head>Grant; Fornham, etc.; 1184-1211</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> [<placeName key="place_105024">Fornham</placeName>]
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Samson</forename>, the abbot of <orgName role="abbot" key="org_104015">St. Edmund</orgName></persName>, 
                  grants to <persName>
                           <forename>Ailmar</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>Ailward</forename> de <surname>Fornham</surname></persName></persName>, 
                  the mill which is called '<placeName type="minor">Ailmeres Heine</placeName>' at a rent of 30s.; 
                  also a little meadow at the head of the mill-pond, [which mill used to pay an annual rent of 26s.] 
                  for which he is to render to the hall of <placeName key="place_105024">Fornham</placeName> the customary rent of seven
                  ploughshares, with leave to have no ewer free from feldage, to hold the same by heirship. 
                  (<origDate notBefore="1184" notAfter="1211">1184-1211</origDate>.) 
                  </p>
